# Bari Cursor Rules

Cursor is an implementation agent, not a brand designer.

Before coding:
1. Read the requested scope.
2. Identify exact files to edit.
3. Do not redesign unrelated sections.
4. Do not invent new visual concepts unless explicitly requested.
5. Do not add decorative animations unless explicitly requested.
6. Preserve existing routes and architecture.
7. Use real product data/assets where available.
8. Never expose internal BSIP2/debug terminology to users.
9. Run `npm run lint` and `npm run build` after changes.
10. Summarize exact files changed.

## Bari visual direction

- Structured food intelligence
- Product comparison as the visual identity
- Editorial, calm, premium
- Off-white / graphite / soft emerald
- No floating products
- No orbit/dome visuals
- No neon/cyber style
- No generic wellness blog tone
